00DFBC  2               ; RND(n), 32 bit Galoise version. make n=0 for 19th next number in sequence or n<>0
00DFBC  2               ; to get 19th next number in sequence after seed n. This version of the PRNG uses
00DFBC  2               ; the Galois method and a sample of 65536 bytes produced gives the following values.
00DFBC  2               
00DFBC  2               ; Entropy = 7.997442 bits per byte
00DFBC  2               ; Optimum compression would reduce these 65536 bytes by 0 percent
00DFBC  2               
00DFBC  2               ; Chi square distribution for 65536 samples is 232.01, and
00DFBC  2               ; randomly would exceed this value 75.00 percent of the time
00DFBC  2               
00DFBC  2               ; Arithmetic mean value of data bytes is 127.6724, 127.5 would be random
00DFBC  2               ; Monte Carlo value for Pi is 3.122871269, error 0.60 percent
00DFBC  2               ; Serial correlation coefficient is -0.000370, totally uncorrelated would be 0.0
00DFBC  2               
